{"key":"processedPost-8811781","value":{"id":8811781,"first":8810843,"last":8813105,"when":1219440379,"utime":"08/23/08 12:26 AM","cleanedPost":"Disregard at least half the responses in this thread.&nbsp; They're flat out wrong.<br />You can mist and/or fan any type of growing chamber you want to.&nbsp; Fresh air exchange is one of the main pinning triggers.&nbsp; Rubbermaid tubs do not have an airtight lid, so the polyfil does nothing to keep contamination out of a monotub.&nbsp; It simply slows down the rate of evaporation from the substrate.&nbsp; However, evaporation from the substrate is another major pinning trigger, so increasing air exchange, and then increasing misting to make up for the lost moisture is going to increase results over the 'set it and forget it' plan.&nbsp; Some strains are more CO2 tolerant than others, and these work fine in a semi-sealed tub, but others perform poorly.<br />RR"}}